.SH NAME
line \- read one line
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B line
.SH DESCRIPTION
.I Line
copies one line from standard input to standard output.
If end-of-file is reached on input or if a read error occurs,
its exit status is non-zero.
.I Line
always writes a newline as the last character.
